title: The Front Page - 1974
description:
ORIGINAL TITLE: The Front Page 
YEAR: 1974   
 
RUNNING TIME: 105 min. 
COUNTRY: USA 
DIRECTOR: Billy Wilder 
SCREENWRITER: Billy Wilder & I.A.L. Diamond (Play: Ben Hecht & Charles MacArthur) 
COMPOSER: Billy May 
CINEMATOGRAPHER: Jordan Cronenweth 
CAST: Jack Lemmon, Walter Matthau, Susan Sarandon, Carol Burnett, Allen Garfield, David Wayne, Vincent Gardenia, Herbert Edelman, Charles Durning, Martin Gabel, Austin Pendleton 

Hildy Johnson is the top reporter on a Chicago newspaper during the 1920s. Tired of the whole game he&#039;s determined to quit his job to get married. His scheming editor, Walter Burns, has other plans though. It&#039;s the day before guilty (but insane) murderer, Earl Williams, is due to go to the gallows and Burns tempts Johnson to stay and write the story.
